sentences: Wolfgang Plagge (born 23 August 1960 in Oslo, Norway by Dutch parents) is a Norwegian composer and pianist.
1996 saw Plagge being bestowed with the Composer of the Year Award by the Trondheim Symphony Orchestra.
In 2001 he received an ASCAP Award and he won the Vocal Nord’s composers competition in 2003.
In 2001 he received an ASCAP Award and he won the Vocal Nord’s composers competition in 2003.

In 2007 he was the recipient of the Hungarian The international cultural order of knights of St. Stefan which is Hungary's highest civilian honor for his work on promoting Hungarian music and culture in the Nordic countries, as well as his work with the teaching technique of Zoltán Kodály.

Plagge started playing the piano as four years old, and made a sensational recital debut in the University Hall in Oslo, only twelve years old.
Plagge has since he was 8 years been organist and eventually Cantor in Asker and Bærum congregation of The Catholic Church in Stabekk, Norway.
